    E1684 Melanoma Clinical Trial.

    e1684.Rd

    Two-arm phase III clinical trial conducted by the Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) to comparing high-dose interferon (IFN) to observation (OBS). There were a total of 286 patients diagnosed with melanoma enrolled in the study, which accrued from 1984 to 1990, and the study was unblinded in 1993.

    Format

    A data frame with 286 rows and 10 variables:

    • trt: treatment (1 - observation, 2 - IFN)

    • failtime: time to relapse from randomization

    • failcens: failure indicator (1 - failure; 0 - otherwise)

    • survtime: time from relapse to death

    • survcens: failure indicator (1 - failure; 0 - otherwise)

    • age: patient's age (in years)

    • node: 4 nodal categories

    • sex: patient's (0=male, 1=female)

    • ps: patient's performance status (0 - fully active; 1 - other)

    • breslow: Breslow depth (in mm)

    References

    Ibrahim JG, Chen MH, Sinha D (2001). Bayesian Survival Analysis, volume 1. Springer, New York, NY.
